‘Right from the beginning her mum 
Dolly was so supportive. We had to separate Hope from her mum while the 
procedure was carried out but she watched over the fence the whole time.

‘It is fantastic to see Hope walking completely normally now. One of her favourite things to do is chase squirrels and birds.

'We
are all very ecstatic that the procedure worked and it looks as though 
this sweet little giraffe will live an otherwise normal life.’

